response.overview: In 1982 the Milwaukee Brewers led the league in runs and home runs and earned the nickname Harvey's Wallbangers (A reference to their manager Harvey Kuenn). They beat the California Angels in the American League Championship and went on to play the St. Louis Cardinals in the World Series. Relive this magical year through the eyes of those that were there including Paul Molitor Robin Yount Rollie Fingers Jim Gatner and more! Narrated by the voice of the Brewers Bob Uecker.
response.title: Harvey's Wallbangers: The 1982 Milwaukee Brewers
